title: Nemesis Now Norse Mythology Decor Bronze God Statue 8.5cm Tall – Cast in The Finest Resin, Expertly Hand-Painted – Thor God of Thunder and Lightning
features: Mini Thor 4.5*3.5*8.5cm: Embrace the power and majesty of Thor, the revered god of thunder and lightning, with this exquisite miniature bronze figurine

Thor - God of Thunder and Lightning Miniature Bronze Figurine: This piece features Thor wielding his iconic hammer, Mjölnir, in a commanding pose, given a polished bronze finish which highlights its premium craftsmanship, capturing the essence of the Norse deity in a beautifully crafted miniature polished bronze finish highlight its premium craftsmanship, capturing the essence of the Norse deity in a beautifully crafted miniature

Part of Nemesis Now's Mythology Range: A perfect gift for enthusiasts of Norse mythology or collectors of mythical artifacts, this Thor God of Thunder and Lightning figurine is a standout piece in Nemesis Now’s mythology range
Cast in the Finest Polished Bronze Resin: Crafted with meticulous attention to detail, this figurine is cast in high-quality bronze resin, polished to enhance the figurine's rich bronze finish

Mythology: Legends, folklore and myths are the foundations to all of our cultures- without these, our traditions would die with the generations that have long since passed, so celebrate their stories with Nemesis Now's mythological collection
description: From the manufacturer Historic & Medieval Ranges Are Vikings your thing? Then, explore our Drakkar and Danegeld range. What about Anglo and Celtic history? You can explore our Heraldic and The Brave range here. Danegeld Viking Range Honour the Norse Gods with our exclusive range of the Viking merchandise. Inspired by the Nordic warriors of old, all feature hints of their history from the carved wood of the Skeid, symbols of the futhark or weapons from battle. Pay homage to the old ways and earn your rightful place in Valhalla today! Mother, Maiden & Crone Backflow Incense Burner Illustrating the stages of life, a young maiden, a pregnant woman and an elderly lady all stand holding a chalice. Each wears a hooded gown with intricate root networks emblazoned on them. The base is formed from twisted branches and below, each woman is their phase of the moon, either a crescent moon and a full moon. Goblet of the Brave The Goblet is backed by intricate silver thistle patterns as 6 shields are raised from the curved sides. Alternating Robert the Bruce, Saltire and White Thistle shields as separated by long swords. The stem is very simplistic, featuring the vine of a singular thistle, yet the base is decorated with the same intricate patterns that feature on the Goblet. Sword in The Stone Letter Opener Cast in high-quality bronze, the legendary king of the Britons stands in shining armour with one foot planted on the stone, his cape behind him. He grips the legendary sword in his hands, preparing to free it - and now you can too, using it to open your post and packages!
